  "description": "Figure-Eight topology at macroKnot=0.5 — the chimera midpoint between Figure-Eight and Torus. At this exact interpolation, the coupling matrix carries both the alternating polarity of the Figure-Eight (over/under crossing) and the surface symmetry of the Torus simultaneously. Neither topology alone; both at once. LFO1 on braid depth at 1.8 Hz creates a rhythmic coupling accent: at 120 BPM this crosses WEAVE-I approximately every two 16th notes. Notes voiced at the LFO peak have full chimera character; notes at the trough breathe in gentle chorus. The accent is topological, not velocity.",
